main event: A large, round, brilliant light was observed illuminating an area from 60 miles away in Winslow, Arizona on February 24, 1963.
interesting points: The sighting lasted between 10 to 15 minutes., The object was seen traveling in a straight course., It was concluded to possibly be a balloon or astronomical body., There were limited attempts to collect additional data or evidence., This report came from a Project Blue Book investigation.
witness description: The sighting was reported third hand and did not specify witnesses.
